<subSubSection box="[151,350,439,465]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,350,439,465]" box="[151,350,439,465]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,350,439,465]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,439,465]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Clade 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koslowsky" authorityYear="1896" box="[231,350,439,465]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,350,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,514,740]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Recent phylogenetic evidence (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Espinoza" box="[571,814,514,540]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Espinoza" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="16819 - 16824" refId="ref59093" refString="Espinoza, R. E., Wiens, J. J. &amp; Tracy, C. R. (2004) Recurrent evolution of herbivory in small, cold-climate lizards: Breaking the ecophysiological rules or reptilian herbivory. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, USA, 101, 16819 - 16824." type="journal article" year="2004">
Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[686,745,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala" box="[827,979,514,540]" firstAuthor="Abdala" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala 2007</bibRefCitation>
) suggests that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koslowsky" authorityYear="1896" box="[1154,1299,514,539]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anomalus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1299,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cei" authorityYear="1983" box="[1314,1429,514,539]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ditadai">
<emphasis box="[1314,1429,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. ditadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cei" authorityYear="1978" box="[151,298,554,579]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duellmani">
<emphasis box="[151,298,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. duellmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cei" authorityYear="1981" box="[355,582,554,579]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pseudoanomalus">
<emphasis box="[355,582,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">L. pseudoanomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might form a natural group closely related to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koslowsky" authorityYear="1898" box="[1160,1287,554,579]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boulengeri">
<emphasis box="[1160,1287,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">boulengeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (or even a phylogenetic line nested within this complex; e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso" box="[858,1228,594,620]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="25 - 42" refId="ref70157" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D., Scolaro, J. A. &amp; Schulte II, J. A. (2007 a) The limits of polymorphism in Liolaemus rothi: molecular and phenotypic evidence for a new species of the Liolaemus boulengeri clade (Iguanidae, Liolaemini) from boreal Patagonia of Chile. Zootaxa, 1452, 25 - 42." type="journal article" year="2007" yearSuffix="a">
Pincheira-Donoso 
<emphasis box="[1080,1143,594,619]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2007a
</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala" firstAuthor="Abdala" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Although we recognize that further studies might be needed to support Espinoza 
<emphasis box="[1215,1276,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
’s (2004) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Abdala, C. S." box="[151,341,674,700]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref50199" refString="Abdala, C. S. (2007) Phylogeny of the boulengeri group (Iguania: Liolaemidae, Liolaemus) based on morphological and molecular characters. Zootaxa, 1538, 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="2007">Abdala’s (2007)</bibRefCitation>
phylogenetic hypotheses with additional evidence, we also recognize their value, and hence, this is the position we adopt in our work.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
